---
import DocsLayout from "../../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro";
---

<DocsLayout>
  <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 py-8 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 text-white">
    <section
      class="text-center mb-12 p-8 bg-linear-to-r from-blue-700/30 to-cyan-300/40 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/20 backdrop-blur-sm"
    >
      <div class="flex items-center justify-center gap-3 mb-4">
        <svg
          xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
          class=" size-10"
          viewBox="0 0 24 24"
          fill="none"
          stroke="cyan"
          stroke-width="2"
          stroke-linecap="round"
          stroke-linejoin="round"
          class="icon icon-tabler icons-tabler-outline icon-tabler-spacing-horizontal"
          ><path stroke="none" d="M0 0h24v24H0z" fill="none"></path><path
            d="M20 20h-2a2 2 0 0 1 -2 -2v-12a2 2 0 0 1 2 -2h2"></path><path
            d="M4 20h2a2 2 0 0 0 2 -2v-12a2 2 0 0 0 -2 -2h-2"></path><path
            d="M12 8v8"></path></svg
        >
        <h1
          class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-white bg-linear-to-r from-cyan-400 to-blue-400 bg-clip-text"
        >
          Spacing in Tailwind CSS
        </h1>
      </div>

      <p class="text-body/90 text-lg leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Learn how to effectively use spacing utilities in Tailwind CSS to create
        visually appealing and well-structured layouts.
      </p>

      <div class="bg-blue-950/30 border-l-4 border-blue-400 p-4 rounded-lg">
        <p class="text-blue-200 text-sm">
          ðŸ’¡ <strong>Why use Spacing?</strong> Consistent spacing creates visual harmony
          and improves readability in your UI.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-6 flex items-center gap-2">
        <svg
          class="w-7 h-7 text-cyan-400"
          fill="none"
          stroke="currentColor"
          viewBox="0 0 24 24"
        >
          <path
            stroke-linecap="round"
            stroke-linejoin="round"
            stroke-width="2"
            d="M4 8V4m0 0h4M4 4l5 5m11-1V4m0 0h-4m4 0l-5 5M4 16v4m0 0h4m-4 0l5-5m11 5l-5-5m5 5v-4m0 4h-4"
          ></path>
        </svg>
        Custom Spacing & Sizing
      </h2>

      <div
        class="bg-neutral-secondary-soft p-6 rounded-lg border border-default bg-linear-to-br from-cyan-400/20 to-blue-500/20"
      >
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-cyan-400 mb-3">
            Adding Custom spacing
        </h3>
        <p class="text-body/80 mb-4">
          Add custom spacing values for margin, padding, width, and height:
        </p>

        <div class="bg-black/30 p-4 rounded-lg mb-4">
          <pre
            class="text-sm text-cyan-200"><code>{`export default {
  theme: {
    extend: {
      spacing: {
        '18': '4.5rem',   // 72px
        '88': '22rem',    // 352px
        '128': '32rem',   // 512px
      },
      maxWidth: {
        '8xl': '88rem',
        '9xl': '96rem',
      },
      height: {
        'screen-1/2': '50vh',
        'screen-3/4': '75vh',
      },
    },
  },
}`}</code></pre>
        </div>

        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
          <div class="bg-black/20 p-4 rounded-lg">
            <p class="text-cyan-300 text-sm mb-2">Usage examples:</p>
            <div class="space-y-2 text-sm text-body/80">
              <div>
                <code class="bg-black/30 px-2 py-0.5 rounded text-cyan-300"
                  >mt-18</code
                > â†’ margin-top: 4.5rem
              </div>
              <div>
                <code class="bg-black/30 px-2 py-0.5 rounded text-cyan-300"
                  >max-w-8xl</code
                > â†’ max-width: 88rem
              </div>
              <div>
                <code class="bg-black/30 px-2 py-0.5 rounded text-cyan-300"
                  >h-screen-1/2</code
                > â†’ height: 50vh
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div
            class="bg-black/20 p-4 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center"
          >
            <div
              class="w-18 h-18 bg-linear-to-br from-cyan-500 to-blue-500 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center text-white text-sm"
            >
              w-18 h-18
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</DocsLayout>
